    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Windshield Wiper Assembly</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Windshield Wiper Assembly</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove both driver and passenger side windshield wiper arm and blade assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603802.xml" xrefid="x1603802">
                        <emph type="bold">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603802"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cab cowl tray. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603809.xml" xrefid="x1603809">
                        <emph type="bold">CAB COWL TRAY</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603809"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603845" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603845.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Windshield Wiper Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING STUDS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WINDSHIELD WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WINDSHIELD WIPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If needed, cut wire tie securing wiring harness to windshield wiper motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector from windshield wiper motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four mounting nuts from the mounting studs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove windshield wiper assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install windshield wiper assembly onto the four mounting studs and secure with four
                    mounting nuts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603845">Figure 64, Items 1, 2, and 5</hotlnk>). Tighten nuts to 16 Lbf-ft (22 N&#8226;m),
                    DO NOT exceed 18 Lbf-ft (24 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect electrical connector to windshield wiper motor (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603845">Figure 64, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, secure wiring harness and connector with wire tie.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the cab cowl tray. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603809.xml" xrefid="x1603809">
                        <emph type="bold">CAB COWL TRAY</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603809"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install driver and passenger side windshield wiper arm and blade assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603802.xml" xrefid="x1603802">
                        <emph type="bold">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603802"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn wipers on high speed, activate windshield washer, and check for proper wiper
                    operation. If required, adjust windshield wiper arm and blade assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
